# Plan Gate — TeleHealthy

## Review

**Concept clarity:** Single-screen Voice Ops Console with 4 tabs. Clear, scoped, demonstrable. ✓

**Requirements traceability:** All 6 explicit reqs (inbound handler, booking, FAQ, SMS confirmation, outbound dialer, analytics + transcripts) traced to named components. 3 nice-to-haves (healthcare language, automation viz, multilingual EN/ES) covered. ✓

**Prototype vs Full decision:** Justified. Hero feature (WebGPU in-browser LLM) is client-side; no backend needed; scripted fallback handles GPU-unavailable cases. ✓

**Design system:** Fully locked (palette with 9 tokens, fonts Inter + DM Mono, layout described). ✓

**Tech stack:** Vite + React 18 + WebLLM (@mlc-ai/web-llm), base path set, build output path set. ✓

**File plan:** 12 files (at cap). Each file has a clear purpose. No overlap, no missing pieces. ✓

**Feature richness vs target (10/10):** 4 working tabs, real WebGPU AI with deterministic fallback, booking flow, FAQ (EN/ES), escalation logic, SMS log, outbound dynamic scripting, analytics dashboard (charts + KPIs + transcript list), CRM contact table, automation pipeline viz, multilingual toggle. Adequate for a 10/10 target. ✓

**Research questions:** 5 scoped, answerable questions (WebLLM CDN import, model ID, WebGPU flags, Vapi/Retell UI conventions, GoHighLevel fields). Well within 6-fetch cap. These are forward-looking items for the researcher step — not gaps that invalidate the plan. ✓

**Risks acknowledged:** Model download size (mitigated by lazy-load + scripted fallback), WebGPU browser support (mitigated by navigator.gpu guard). ✓

## Problems Found

None. No unfilled requirements, no contradictions, no unresolved architectural choices that block researcher or demo-builder.

## handoff
- produced: gate check result — plan reviewed against all criteria
- decisions: plan passes; research questions are scoped for researcher, not blocking the plan
- next needs: researcher addresses the 5 flagged questions (WebLLM CDN/model ID is most critical — demo-builder cannot write useWebLLM.js without the exact import string)
- risks: WebLLM model ID must be verified before demo-builder starts; incorrect ID = runtime 404 on model fetch

VERDICT: pass
